# vscode-calcpad build environment (example)
#
# These variables are read by scripts/sync-bundled-server.mjs (via process.env)
# at BUILD time — i.e. when you run `npm run sync-server*` / `npm run package*`.
# The script does NOT auto-load this file. Either export the variables in your
# shell (`setx NAME value` on Windows persists them for future sessions) or
# source this file with your own tooling. Copy to `.env` and fill in as needed.
#
# All signing vars are optional: if CALCPAD_SIGN_THUMBPRINT is unset, the build
# produces a working *unsigned* bundle (correct for CI and for contributors who
# don't have a signing cert).

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Apphost code signing
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Why: a freshly-built, unsigned Calcpad.Server.exe has no cloud reputation, so
# Windows Defender / SmartScreen / corporate EDR can block it from running
# (block-at-first-sight). Reputation is tracked per-file-hash for unsigned
# binaries — so it re-fires on every rebuild — but per-PUBLISHER for signed
# ones. Signing with a trusted cert makes rebuilds trusted immediately.
#
# Only the native apphost (.exe) is signed; the managed .dll files load through
# it. See signApphost() in scripts/sync-bundled-server.mjs.

# SHA1 thumbprint of a code-signing cert in the current user's store
# (Cert:\CurrentUser\My). When set, the build signs bin/Calcpad.Server.exe.
# Create a self-signed dev cert with:
#   New-SelfSignedCertificate -Type CodeSigningCert -Subject 'CN=Calcpad Dev Signing' \
#     -KeyUsage DigitalSignature -KeyExportPolicy Exportable \
#     -CertStoreLocation Cert:\CurrentUser\My -NotAfter (Get-Date).AddYears(5)
# then trust it (elevated, one time) by importing the exported .cer into both
# Cert:\LocalMachine\Root and Cert:\LocalMachine\TrustedPublisher.
# CALCPAD_SIGN_THUMBPRINT=59313AFB0FE2268F4A6A901ECA5DBBA98FBEE11B

# Optional: full path to signtool.exe. Only needed if it isn't auto-discovered
# under "C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10\bin\<ver>\x64\signtool.exe".
# CALCPAD_SIGNTOOL=C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10\bin\10.0.19041.0\x64\signtool.exe

# Optional: RFC 3161 timestamp server (default: http://timestamp.digicert.com).
# Timestamping keeps signatures valid after the cert expires.
# CALCPAD_SIGN_TIMESTAMP_URL=http://timestamp.digicert.com
